-- Silver Lake to pay $29.5 mln in LBO collusion settlement
-- By Jonathan Stempel in New York
-- Fri Jul 11, 2014 10:45AM EDT
-- None



July 11 (Reuters) - Silver Lake Partners LP agreed to pay $29.5 million to settle a lawsuit that accused it and several other large private equity firms of conspiring not to outbid each other on takeovers prior to the financial crisis, court records showed.

The settlement was disclosed in a filing late Thursday in  federal court in Boston.